---
description: Rules for creating DetailViews with TailwindCSS styling and Alpine.js interactivity.
globs: **/views.py
---
- All DetailView classes should use appropriate template names
- Detail view templates should extend base.html for consistent layout
- Detail view templates must use TailwindCSS utility classes for styling
- Use standard Django URL patterns and links for navigation
- "Back to List" buttons in detail views should use standard Django links or Alpine.js for enhanced interactivity
- Detail views should include a header with title and "Back to List" button
- Use TailwindCSS card/styling patterns for organizing detail information
- Use Alpine.js for interactive elements within detail views (e.g., expandable sections, tabs)

Example DetailView pattern:
```python
class MyModelDetailView(DetailView):
    """Detail view for MyModel."""
    
    model = MyModel
    context_object_name = "mymodel"
    template_name = "app/mymodel_detail.html"
```

Example detail template pattern:
```html
